        <description>
            <geninfo>
                <para>Since the introduction of the International High Performance Vehicles (HPV), the air filter
                    mounted air restriction gauge has used a "Push To Connect" fitting for mounting. Some units may
                    experience the air restriction gauge falling out of its "Push To Connect" mounting. If this occurs,
                    the installation of a "wave" washer between the "Push To Connect" release collar and air filter
                    housing will prevent further occurrences.
                </para>
            </geninfo>
        </description>
        <partsinfo>
            <para>Wave Washer 2588492C1</para>
        </partsinfo>
        <svcproc svcproctype="repair" graphiccount="1">
            <title>service Procedure</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>To avoid property damage, personal injury, or death, park the vehicle on a flat level surface,
                        set the parking brake, turn the engine off, and chock the wheels.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Remove the air restriction gauge from the air filter housing by pushing the release
                    collar on the "Push To Connect" fitting and removing the air restriction gauge.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Use a small screwdriver or pliers to gently remove the "Push To Connect" release collar
                    from the air filter housing.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Install wave washer Part Number 2588492C1 over the "Push To Connect" release collar and
                    reinstall release collar into air filter housing. Make certain that release collar "snaps" into
                    position as shown in Figure 1.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Reinstall the air restriction gauge into the "Push To Connect" release collar. Make
                    certain the air restriction gauge will not pull out of the fitting without first pushing the release
                    collar.
                </para>
            </step1>
